06/05/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- The Turkish Parliament continues discussing a package on key draft constitutional changes proposed by the ruling Justice and Development Party with the purpose of settling the current political crisis in the country, local media reported at the weekend. 
If the adjustments pass the legislature and are ratified by outgoing President Ahmet Necdet Sezer, the first round of direct presidential elections could take place on July 22nd, together with the early parliamentary vote. 
(Zaman, Radikal, Anadolu Agency, Focus, BTA - 05/05/07)
